'''ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱯᱨᱚᱠᱟᱥ ᱵᱷᱚᱜᱚᱛ'''<ref>{{Cite web|title=Chetan Bhagat tweets his CBSE Class 10 mark sheet|url=https://www.educationworld.in/chetan-bhagat-tweets-his-cbse-class-10-mark-sheet/|date=3 August 2019|website=EducationWorld|access-date=25 May 2020}}</ref> (ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱒᱒ ᱚᱯᱨᱮᱞ ᱑᱙᱗᱔) ᱫᱚ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ. ᱚᱱᱚᱞᱤᱭᱟ., ᱠᱟ.ᱦᱱᱤ ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱠᱟᱨ, [[ᱵᱚᱞᱤᱣᱩᱰ]] ᱥᱨᱤᱱ ᱨᱟᱭᱴᱚᱨ, ᱥᱳᱥᱤᱭᱟᱞ ᱢᱮᱰᱤᱭᱟ ᱤᱱᱯᱷᱩᱭᱮᱱᱥᱚᱨ(social media influencer) ᱟᱨ ᱢᱳᱴᱤᱵᱮᱥᱚᱱᱟᱞ ᱯᱷᱳᱠᱚᱨ(motivational speaker) ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱫᱚ ᱒᱐᱑᱐ ᱨᱮ [[ᱴᱟᱭᱤᱢ ᱢᱟᱜᱟᱡᱤᱱ]] ᱯᱟᱦᱴᱟ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱥᱟᱯᱲᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱱ ᱡᱮᱜᱮᱛ ᱨᱮᱱ ᱑᱐᱐ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱡᱟ.ᱥᱛᱤ ᱤᱱᱯᱷᱞᱩᱭᱮᱱᱥᱤᱭᱟᱞ(Influential) ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ ᱛᱟᱞᱟᱨᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱫᱚᱲᱚᱢ ᱞᱮᱫᱮᱭᱟ ᱾<ref name=Time>{{cite web |title=The 2010 TIME 100 |url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/packages/completelist/0,29569,1984685,00.html |website=Time |accessdate=26 November 2019}}</ref>

ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱵᱷᱚᱜᱚᱛ [[ᱤᱱᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱤᱱᱥᱴᱤᱪᱭᱩᱴ ᱚᱯᱷ ᱢᱮᱠᱱᱳᱞᱳᱡᱤ|ᱟᱭ.ᱟᱭ.ᱴᱩ.]], ᱫᱤᱞᱞᱤ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱢᱮᱠᱟᱱᱤᱠᱟᱞ ᱤᱸᱡᱤᱱᱤᱭᱚᱨᱤᱝ ᱨᱮ ᱵᱤ.ᱴᱮᱠ ᱰᱤᱜᱽᱨᱤ ᱦᱟᱛᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱫᱟ ᱟᱨ [[ᱤᱱᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱤᱱᱥᱴᱤᱪᱭᱩᱴ ᱚᱯᱷ ᱢᱮᱱᱮᱡᱽᱢᱮᱸᱴ|ᱟᱭ.ᱟᱭ.ᱮᱢ.]], ᱚᱦᱚᱢᱚᱫᱟᱵᱟᱫᱽ ᱠᱷᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱮᱢ.ᱵᱤ.ᱮ. ᱠᱚᱨᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱫᱟ ᱾ ᱢᱤᱫ ᱤᱱᱵᱷᱮᱥᱴᱢᱮᱸᱴ ᱵᱮᱸᱠ ᱠᱷᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱪᱟ.ᱠᱨᱤ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ᱮ ᱮᱦᱚᱵ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱛᱚᱵᱮ ᱚᱱᱚᱞᱤᱭᱟ. ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱣ ᱥᱟᱱᱟᱭᱮ ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱪᱟ.ᱠᱨᱤ ᱵᱟ.ᱜᱤᱟᱫ-ᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱤᱨᱟ.ᱞ ᱜᱚᱴᱮᱡ ᱱᱳᱵᱮᱞ,ᱯᱮᱭᱟ ᱱᱚᱱ-ᱯᱷᱤᱠᱥᱚᱱ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ-ᱮ ᱚᱞ ᱟᱠᱟᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱡᱷᱚᱛᱚ ᱠᱷᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱧᱩᱛᱩᱢᱟᱱ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ [[ᱯᱷᱟᱭᱤᱵᱽ ᱯᱚᱭᱮᱸᱴ ᱥᱚᱢᱣᱟᱱ]] ᱫᱚ ᱒᱐᱐᱔ ᱨᱮ ᱨᱤᱞᱤᱡᱽ ᱞᱮᱱ ᱛᱟᱭᱟ ᱾ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱜᱮ ᱪᱟᱢᱯᱷᱮᱞ ᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ ᱚᱱᱟᱛᱮ ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱵᱷᱚᱜᱟᱛ ᱫᱚ "ᱡᱟ.ᱥᱛᱤ ᱟ.ᱠᱷᱨᱤᱧ ᱟᱠᱟᱱ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱤᱝᱞᱤᱥ ᱱᱳᱵᱮᱞ ᱚᱱᱚᱞᱤᱭᱟ."‌ ᱠᱚ ᱢᱮᱛᱟᱦᱟᱭᱟ ᱾<ref>{{Cite web|title=A Conversation with Chetan Bhagat, the biggest selling English language novelist in India’s history.|url=https://thoughteconomics.com/|last=MBE|first=Vikas Shah|date=31 May 2019|website=Thought Economics|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> ᱡᱟᱦᱟᱸᱭᱮᱱ ᱜᱮ, ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱚᱱᱚᱞ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱠᱚ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱟ.ᱰᱤ ᱛᱮᱫ ᱜᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱞᱟᱱᱫᱟ ᱚᱴᱟᱝ-ᱟ, ᱠᱤᱪᱷᱩ ᱫᱚ ᱠᱚ ᱢᱮᱱ-ᱟ ᱵᱷᱟ.ᱜᱤ ᱞᱮᱠᱟ ᱚᱞ ᱵᱟᱭ ᱵᱟᱰᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ ᱠᱤᱪᱷᱩ ᱫᱚ ᱠᱚ ᱢᱮᱱ-ᱟ ᱡᱮᱢᱚᱱ ᱨᱚᱱᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱥᱮ ᱥᱟᱶᱦᱮᱫ ᱠᱚ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱚᱞ ᱵᱟᱭ ᱵᱟᱰᱟᱭᱟ ᱾<ref>{{Cite web|title=Why I gave Chetan Bhagat the 'nastiest review'|url=https://www.dailyo.in/arts/chetan-bhagat-one-indian-girl-catcher-in-the-rye-open-novelist-toi-feminism/story/1/13537.html|website=dailyo.in|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ''[[ᱣᱟᱱ ᱤᱱᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱜᱟᱞ|<nowiki/>'One Indian Girl'<nowiki/>]]'' ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱦᱚᱸ ᱟ.ᱰᱤᱜᱮ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱟ ᱠᱩᱥᱤᱭᱟᱫ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸᱫ ᱾<ref>{{Cite web|title=Chetan Bhagat accused of plagiarising his latest bestseller, One Indian Girl|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/books/chetan-bhagat-accused-of-plagiarising-his-latest-bestseller-one-indian-girl/story-1DLX2bx5PYZQQdGmhFUekK.html|date=25 April 2017|website=Hindustan Times|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Sales of Chetan Bhagat’s ‘One Indian Girl’ stopped by injunction, on plagiarism charges|url=https://scroll.in/latest/835550/chetan-bhagats-one-indian-girl-ordered-out-of-bookstores-on-plagiarism-charges|website=Scroll.in|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref>

ᱮᱯᱨᱤᱞ ᱒᱐᱑᱗ ᱨᱮ, ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱯᱚᱛᱟᱵ ''[[ᱯᱷᱟᱭᱤᱵᱽ ᱯᱚᱭᱮᱸᱴ ᱥᱚᱢᱣᱟᱱ|<nowiki/>'Five Point Someone'<nowiki/>]]'', [[ᱫᱤᱞᱞᱤ ᱡᱮᱜᱮᱛ ᱵᱤᱨᱫᱟ.ᱜᱟᱲ]] ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱤᱝᱞᱤᱥ ᱰᱤᱯᱟᱴᱢᱮᱸᱴ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫ ᱵᱟᱠᱷᱨᱟ ᱵᱤᱵᱟ.ᱫᱽ ᱮᱦᱚᱵᱽ ᱞᱮᱱᱟ ᱾ <ref>{{Cite web|title=Chetan Bhagat’s Five Point Someone in Delhi University English literature syllabus|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/delhi/chetan-bhagat-s-five-point-someone-in-delhi-university-english-literature-syllabus/story-JVRGnIQX5C7oGkaLnfysIN.html|date=24 April 2017|website=Hindustan Times|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Chetan Bhagat's Five Point Someone To Be Part Of DU's English Literature Syllabus|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/chetan-bhagats-five-point-someone-to-be-part-of-dus-english-literature-syllabus/298646|website=outlookindia.com/|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Five Point Someone in DU syllabus: Let’s stop blaming Chetan Bhagat and start rueing the state of Indian readership|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/opinion/web-edits/delhi-university-english-five-point-someone-in-du-syllabus-lets-stop-blaming-chetan-bhagat-and-start-rueing-the-state-of-indian-readership/|date=25 April 2017|website=The Indian Express|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> ᱛᱚᱵᱮ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱜᱟᱱ ᱵᱟᱫᱽ-ᱵᱤᱵᱟ.ᱫᱽ ᱦᱩᱭᱮᱱ ᱫᱚᱥᱟᱨ ᱡᱮᱜᱮᱛ ᱵᱤᱨᱫᱟ.ᱜᱟᱲ ᱯᱟᱦᱴᱟ ᱠᱷᱟᱱ ᱢᱤᱫ ᱜᱟᱞᱚᱪ ᱠᱚ ᱫᱩᱲᱩᱵ ᱠᱚᱣᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱱᱚᱱᱚᱞ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱮᱞᱮᱫᱟ ᱥᱮ ᱵᱟᱝ ᱚᱱᱟᱠᱚ ᱴᱷᱟ.ᱣᱠᱟ‌‌.ᱭᱟ ᱾ <ref>{{Cite web|title='Five Point Someone' not part of DU curriculum this session|url=http://www.millenniumpost.in/delhi/five-point-someone-not-part-of-du-curriculum-this-session-263547|last=MP|first=Team|date=24 September 2017|website=millenniumpost.in|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=DU’s Proposal To Add 'Five Point Someone' in Curriculum Reconsidered|url=https://www.careerindia.com/news/delhi-university-proposal-to-add-five-point-someone-reconsidered-020712.html|last=Malavikka|date=25 September 2017|website=careerindia.com|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱᱟᱜ ᱢᱚᱬᱮ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱚᱱᱚᱞ ᱯᱚᱛᱚᱵ ᱪᱮᱛᱟᱱ ᱨᱮ ᱵᱚᱞᱤᱣᱩᱰ ᱯᱷᱤᱢ ᱠᱚ‌ ᱥᱩᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ, ᱡᱮᱢᱚᱱ ''<nowiki/>'[[ᱦᱮᱞᱳ (᱒᱐᱐᱘ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|ᱦᱮᱞᱳ'<nowiki/>]]'' ᱫᱚ ([[ᱣᱟᱱ ᱱᱟᱭᱤᱴ @ ᱫᱤ ᱠᱚᱞ ᱥᱮᱱᱴᱚᱨ]]); ''[[ᱛᱷᱨᱤ ᱤᱰᱤᱭᱚᱴ|<nowiki/>'3 Idiots'<nowiki/>]]'' ᱫᱚ ᱒᱐᱐᱙ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ([[ᱯᱷᱟᱭᱤᱵᱽ ᱯᱚᱭᱮᱸᱴ ᱥᱚᱢᱣᱟᱱ]]); ''[[ᱠᱳᱭᱤ ᱯᱳᱪᱷᱮ!|<nowiki/>'Kai Po Che'<nowiki/>]]'' ᱫᱚ ᱒᱐᱑᱓ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ([[ᱫᱤ ᱛᱷᱨᱤ ᱢᱤᱥᱴᱮᱠ ᱚᱯᱷ ᱢᱟᱭ ᱞᱟᱭᱤᱯᱷ]]); [[ᱴᱳ ᱥᱴᱮᱴᱥ (᱒᱐᱑᱔ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|'ᱴᱳ ᱥᱴᱮᱴᱥ']] ᱫᱚ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱒᱐᱑᱔ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ([[ᱴᱳ ᱥᱴᱮᱴᱥ: ᱥᱤ ᱥᱴᱳᱨᱤ ᱚᱯᱷ ᱢᱟᱭ ᱢᱮᱨᱮᱡᱽ|ᱴᱳ ᱥᱴᱮᱴᱥ]]); ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱦᱟᱯᱷ ᱜᱟᱞᱯᱷᱨᱮᱸᱰ (ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|<nowiki/>'Half Girlfriend'<nowiki/>]]'' ᱫᱚ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱒᱐᱑᱗ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ([[ᱦᱟᱯᱷ ᱜᱟᱞᱯᱷᱨᱮᱸᱰ]]) ᱮᱢᱟᱱ ᱠᱚ ᱾ ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱫᱚ ᱵᱟᱞᱤᱣᱩᱰ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱠᱚ ᱞᱟ.ᱜᱤᱱ ᱥᱠᱨᱤᱯᱴ ᱦᱟᱸᱭ ᱚᱞ ᱵᱟᱲᱟ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱡᱮᱢᱚᱱ, ''[[ᱠᱳᱭᱤ ᱯᱳᱪᱷᱮ!|<nowiki/>'Kai Po Che'<nowiki/>]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱓) (ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱱᱳᱵᱮᱞ [[ᱫᱤ ᱛᱷᱨᱤ ᱢᱤᱥᱴᱮᱠ ᱚᱯᱷ ᱢᱟᱭ ᱞᱟᱭᱤᱯᱷ]]); ''[[ᱠᱤᱠ (᱒᱐᱑᱔ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|<nowiki/>'Kick'<nowiki/>]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱔) ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱦᱟᱯᱷ ᱜᱟᱞᱯᱷᱨᱮᱸᱰ (ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|<nowiki/>'Half Girlfriend'<nowiki/>]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱗) (ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱚᱱᱚᱞ ᱦᱟᱯᱷ ᱜᱟᱞᱯᱷᱨᱮᱸᱰ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱜᱮ).<ref>{{Cite web|title=Every time Chetan Bhagat made it to Bollywood – A Bollywood Hit!|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/every-time-chetan-bhagat-made-it-to-bollywood/a-bollywood-hit/slideshow/63829137.cms|website=The Economic Times|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> ᱪᱮᱛᱚᱱ ᱯᱩᱵᱟᱞᱤ ᱪᱚᱣᱫᱷᱚᱨᱤ,ᱥᱩᱯᱨᱚᱛᱤᱠ ᱥᱮᱱ ᱟᱨ ᱚᱵᱷᱤᱥᱮᱠ ᱠᱟᱯᱩᱨ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱟᱶ [[ᱠᱚᱭ ᱯᱤ ᱪᱮ]] ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱨᱮ ᱱᱟᱯᱟᱭ ᱥᱠᱨᱤᱯᱴ ᱨᱟᱭᱴᱚᱨ ᱞᱟ.ᱜᱤᱱ [[᱕᱙ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝᱼᱟᱜ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱰ]] ᱒᱐᱑᱔ ᱥᱟ.ᱦᱤᱛ ᱨᱮ ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫᱼᱟ ᱾   <ref>{{Cite web|title=Filmfare Awards Winners From 1953 to 2020|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards/winners|website=filmfare.com|language=en|access-date=2020-05-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Filmfare Awards (2014)|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000245/2014/1/|publisher=IMDb|access-date=23 May 2020}}</ref> 

